  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>Yes</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The main intention of this study is to compare two ultrasound-guided central venous
      catheterization procedures namely: real-time, ultrasound-guided, in plane axillary vein
      catheterization and real-time, ultrasound-guided, out of plane jugular vein catheterization
      in terms of venipuncture, catheterization success, early mechanical complication and
      catheter-related infection rate in mechanically ventilated patients admitted to the intensive
      care unit.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
